## Phase Branching Points

### After Agent 4
AskQuestion id: `transition-after-agent-4`:
- `continue-both`: Run 5 + 6 in parallel
- `continue-5-only` / `continue-6-only`
- `pause-workflow` / `restart-workflow`

### Phase 1 Complete
AskQuestion id: `phase1-complete`:
- `start-phase2` → Step 2B
- `review-outputs` → list files, re-ask
- `done`

### Phase 2 Complete
AskQuestion id: `phase2-complete`:
- `start-phase3` → Step 2C
- `review-outputs` → list files, re-ask
- `done`

### Phase 3 Complete
AskQuestion id: `workflow-complete`:
- `review-all` / `review-phase1` / `review-phase2` / `review-phase3` / `done`

## Transition Protocol (Step-by-Step)

After each agent, AskQuestion id: `transition-after-agent-{X}`:
- `continue-next` / `pause-workflow` / `restart-agent` / `restart-workflow`

## Error Handling

### Missing Dependencies
AskQuestion id: `error-missing-deps`:
- `create-manual`: pause for user to create
- `skip-agent`: continue (may affect quality)
- `stop-workflow`: stop entirely

### Agent Failure
AskQuestion id: `error-agent-failure`:
- `retry-agent` / `skip-agent` / `stop-workflow`

## Resume Protocol

Scan `/0-documentation/`, `/1-problem/`, `/2-solution/`, `/3-delivery/` for existing deliverables.
Show: last completed agent, next pending, found vs missing files.
AskQuestion id: `resume-choice`:
- `continue-from-next` / `restart-from-last` / `fresh-start` / `go-back`

## Pre-Execution Reminder

Before each agent:
```
Guardrails: No invented numbers. Tag estimates as [AI estimation]. Reference sources as [Source: file.md]. Mark assumptions as [Assumption: ...]. Quote first, interpret second.
```
